S'BT customers could save money when making expensive calls from their mobiles using the free BT SmartTalk app.If you\xe2\x80\x99re a Residential BT customer you can now make calls for the same great value as if you were using your BT calling plan, all through your smartphone\xe2\x80\x99s Wi-Fi or mobile data connection.\xef\x83\xbc\tYou can save money making calls to 0800, 0845 and 0870 numbers\xef\x83\xbc\tYou can make calls back to the UK from abroad for the same price you\xe2\x80\x99d pay if you were in your living room.\xef\x83\xbc\tYou can make great value calls without having to top up your Pay-As-You-Go creditKey features of the App:\xef\x83\xbc\tFree app available to all BT Residential customers\xef\x83\xbc\tMake calls from your smartphone using your BT home calling plan\xef\x83\xbc\tSave money on expensive mobile calls to 0800, 0845 & 0870 numbers\xef\x83\xbc\tUse your mobile fearlessly when calling the UK from abroad. But remember, your BT home calling plan stays on the UK time zone!\xef\x83\xbc\tNo need to keep topping up your PAYG credit\xef\x83\xbc\tUp to 5 devices per household; unique BT.com login required per deviceHow the app works:1.\tPlease note: this app is available to residential BT customers only!2.\tDownload the app and complete the sign-up journey; you\xe2\x80\x99ll need to be at home to link your mobile with your home phone and complete your registration.3.\tUp to 5 devices can be registered per household, but a unique BT.com log-in is required per device. You can create an additional log-in during the registration process.4.\tThe BT account holder will be informed of all new registrations and has the ability to manage their BT SmartTalk service online at www.bt.com/mybt/btsmarttalk - including limiting the type of number each user can call, or even blocking new registrations.5.\tYou\xe2\x80\x99ll also need an internet connection! You can make calls over Wi-Fi, whether at home or out-and-about, or using a 3G/4G connection \xe2\x80\x93 Wi-Fi is best as your mobile service provider may charge you for data usage.6.\tPlease note that call quality is dependent on the quality of your Wi-Fi or mobile data connection \xe2\x80\x93 BT SmartTalk will warn you by displaying a message if your signal strength is poor. Problems connecting? Run the \xe2\x80\x98Connection Test\xe2\x80\x99 in the \xe2\x80\x98Help\xe2\x80\x99 section of the app.7.\tCalls made from this app will cost the same as from your home phone, using your BT calling plan rather than your mobile rates or minutes.8.\tPeople will see your mobile number when you call them via the app rather than your home phone number.9.\tYou\xe2\x80\x99ll see all BT SmartTalk calls itemised by user mobile number on your BT bill, including calls made outside of your home calling plan.10.\tFor more information on your BT home calling plan, you\xe2\x80\x99ll need to ask the BT account holder.Recent changes:Minor bug fixes'
